{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-20T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring arrives with a small, spiky ambassador: the European hedgehog, spotted here in France. Part cuddle, part survival gear, this tiny forager is mostly nocturnal and usually solitary, guided mainly by smell and sound. Its job description is simple: roam, sniff through leaf litter and vacuum up invertebrates like worms, beetles, slugs and caterpillars—the kind of snacks that keep ecosystems running and gardeners smiling. When danger shows up, it doesn't negotiate or flee. It curls into a tight ball and lets its spines do the talking.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-IN0774143305_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_EN-IN0774143305_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spring's prickly patrol","Title":"European hedgehog, France","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Its 5,000-7,000 spines are stiff, hollow hairs made of keratin, not true quills like a porcupine's.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=European+hedgehog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260420_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog"},"Ssd":"20260421","Name":"SpringHedgehog","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0774143305","FullDateString":"21 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"There are more than 400 places across the National Park System in the United States that preserve natural and cultural heritage while creating unforgettable outdoor experiences. From coastlines and forests to vast desert landscapes, these protected sites invite exploration, reflection and wonder.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_EN-IN0473512523_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_EN-IN0473512523_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The adventure doesn't end at sundown","Title":"Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah, United States","Copyright":"© Jason Hatfield/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.213604,-109.902534/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.213604,-109.902534;S9;Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Canyonlands+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260419_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva"},"Ssd":"20260420","Name":"SunsetKiva","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0473512523","FullDateString":"20 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Some places greet you gently. Spiti Valley starts by taking your breath away—literally. Sitting above 3,000 metres in Himachal Pradesh near the Tibetan border, this cold desert largely skips rain and goes straight to extremes.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpitiValley2026_EN-IN0228621600_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpitiValley2026_EN-IN0228621600_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A little thin on air, big on impact","Title":"Spiti Valley, Himachal Pradesh","Copyright":"© Rahul Wedpathak/500px/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/32.246815,78.035095/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=32.246815,78.035095;S9;Spiti Valley, Himachal Pradesh&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260419_SpitiValley2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spiti+Valley&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260418_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260419_SpitiValley2026"},"Ssd":"20260419","Name":"SpitiValley2026","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"0228621600","FullDateString":"19 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, on World Heritage Day, attention turns to places that tell humanity's shared story—protected for their exceptional cultural or natural value. One of them rises from volcanic stone on Easter Island, Chile. At Rano Raraku, the slopes of an extinct volcano became the workshop where nearly all of the island's famous moai were carved. The image captures this remarkable quarry, where half-finished figures emerge from the rock, frozen mid-creation.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-IN8684829616_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MaoiStatues_EN-IN8684829616_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"The silence of unfinished giants","Title":"Moai statue quarry, Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-27.127001,-109.292099/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-27.127001,-109.292099;S9;Rano Raraku, Easter Island, Chile&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260418_MaoiStatues\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Heritage+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260417_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260418_MaoiStatues"},"Ssd":"20260418","Name":"MaoiStatues","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"8684829616","FullDateString":"18 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"On 17 April, International Bat Appreciation Day flips its cape to the planet's night shift: bats. With more than 1,400 species on every continent except Antarctica, these winged mammals keep ecosystems balanced. They've been on Earth for over 50 million years, and only three species are true vampires. Found only in the Americas, these bats feed on blood, while the rest survive on insects, fruit, nectar or pollen. In Texas, Bracken Cave can host up to 20 million Mexican free-tailed bats in summer. Many gulp crop pests, cutting pesticide use; others pollinate wild agaves and disperse seeds that help forests rebound.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-IN8520360814_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_EN-IN8520360814_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bat signal: ON","Title":"Grey-headed flying fox carrying her pup, Yarra Bend Park, Australia","Copyright":"© Doug Gimesy/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-37.798065,145.012222/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-37.798065,145.012222;S9;Yarra Bend Park, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bats&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260416_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom"},"Ssd":"20260417","Name":"FlyingFoxMom","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"8520360814","FullDateString":"17 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each spring, Washington's Skagit Valley transforms into a patchwork of colour as the Skagit Valley Tulip Festival celebrates the arrival of bloom season. Throughout April, visitors can explore tulip gardens and farmland lined with vibrant rows of flowers, all framed by mountain views.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-IN3934438603_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_EN-IN3934438603_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Petal parade","Title":"Skagit Valley Tulip Fields, Washington, United States","Copyright":"© Alan Majchrowicz/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/48.5,-122.033/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=48.5,-122.033;S9;Skagit Valley, Washington, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Skagit+Valley+Washington&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260415_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips"},"Ssd":"20260416","Name":"SkagitTulips","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"3934438603","FullDateString":"16 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Art surrounds us. Creativity and self-expression are part of human identity and mould our past and future. While some might dedicate their lives to the arts, others are the recipients of what artists channel. World Art Day on April 15 celebrates this ever-flowing link between artistic creations and society that shapes our cultures.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.VanGoghFields_EN-IN6304322280_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.VanGoghFields_EN-IN6304322280_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"Stepping inside the living canvas","Title":"The Carrières des Lumières exhibit of Vincent van Gogh, Les Baux-de-Provence, France","Copyright":"© Patrick Aventurier/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"World Art Day is held on 15 April to mark the birthday of Leonardo da Vinci, honouring his lasting influence on art and human creativity.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260415_VanGoghFields\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Art+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260414_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260415_VanGoghFields"},"Ssd":"20260415","Name":"VanGoghFields","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"6304322280","FullDateString":"15 Apr, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The spectacled bear, also known as the Andean bear, is the only South American bear of the Ursidae family. Inhabiting the northern and central Andes Mountains, it dwells primarily in forested areas and feeds mainly on shoots and fruit. Pale markings around the eyes often resemble eyeglasses, or 'spectacles,' giving the species its distinctive name.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-IN2726227738_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_EN-IN2726227738_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Spectacles in the wild","Title":"Spectacled bear resting in tree, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Each spectacled bear has unique facial markings, which scientists use to identify and track individuals in the wild.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spectacled+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260427_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear"},"Ssd":"20260428","Name":"AndeanBear","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2726227738","FullDateString":"28 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Designed by architect Giuseppe Mengoni and completed in 1877, the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II in Milan, Italy, is one of the world's oldest and most famous shopping arcades. Located between Piazza del Duomo and Piazza della Scala, it features a stunning glass-and-iron roof and an elegant, octagonal layout. Affectionately known as 'Milan's living room,' the Galleria is home to high-end boutiques, historic cafés such as Caffè Biffi and Camparino in Galleria and renowned restaurants.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-IN2538393019_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_EN-IN2538393019_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Glass with class","Title":"The glass dome of Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy","Copyright":"© PhillipMinnis/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/45.466179,9.18992/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=45.466179,9.18992;S9;Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galleria+Vittorio+Emanuele+II+Milan+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260426_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria"},"Ssd":"20260427","Name":"MilanGalleria","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2538393019","FullDateString":"27 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring brings apple trees to life with clouds of soft pink blossoms. Their delicate petals brighten orchards and hillsides, standing out against clear blue skies as the season shifts from winter towards warmer days. These blooms attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, helping fruit trees produce the apples that will grow later in the year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-IN2309236905_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_EN-IN2309236905_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Bloom boom","Title":"Pink apple blossoms, Avila Beach, California, United States","Copyright":"© Mimi Ditchie Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.177404,-120.733528/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.177404,-120.733528;S9;Avila Beach, California, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Apple+tree&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260425_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260426","Name":"AppleBlossoms","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2309236905","FullDateString":"26 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Penguins usually bring Antarctica to mind, but these endearing flightless seabirds don't always follow the ice. On World Penguin Day, the Galápagos penguins pictured here offer a vivid counterpoint. Found only in the Galápagos Islands—a volcanic archipelago more than 950 kilometres off Ecuador's coast—this species lives farther north than any other penguin. Cool, nutrient‑rich ocean currents make this equatorial habitat possible by supplying food and keeping surrounding waters within survivable temperatures. Compact and agile, these birds spend much of the day in the water to stay cool.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-IN2047471212_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_EN-IN2047471212_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Breaking the penguin rules","Title":"Galápagos penguins swimming, Galápagos Islands, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Henley Spiers/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-0.859397,-91.215904/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-0.859397,-91.215904;S9;Galápagos Islands, Ecuador&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Penguin+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260424_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins"},"Ssd":"20260425","Name":"GalapagosPenguins","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"2047471212","FullDateString":"25 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What happens when water moves too slowly to notice? In Everglades National Park, it shapes everything. Covering around 6,100 square kilometres, the park was established in 1947 to protect a wetland system unlike any other in the United States. As a recognised UNESCO World Heritage Site, the park's elevated pinelands rise above the marshes and prairies that form one of the world's largest wetland systems.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-IN1738190990_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_EN-IN1738190990_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The power of taking it slow","Title":"Forest hammock of slash pine and saw palmetto, Everglades National Park, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Mary Liz Austin/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/25.400611,-80.658833/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=25.400611,-80.658833;S9;Everglades National Park, Florida, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Everglades+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260423_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine"},"Ssd":"20260424","Name":"SlashPine","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1738190990","FullDateString":"24 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each 23 April, the curtain rises on the life and legacy of William Shakespeare, a playwright whose words still command the world's literary stage. Shakespeare Day commemorates the anniversary of his death in 1616 and the traditionally accepted date of his birth in 1564—a symbolic pairing that honours a writer whose works reshaped English literature. From the psychological depths of 'Hamlet' to the enduring romance of 'Romeo and Juliet,' his language continues to echo through classrooms, theatres and everyday speech. His plays have been performed in numerous languages worldwide.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-IN1263350288_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HathawayCottage_EN-IN1263350288_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"A cottage full of stories","Title":"Anne Hathaway's cottage and garden, Stratford-upon-Avon, England","Copyright":"© David Steele/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/52.190984,-1.732059/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=52.190984,-1.732059;S9;Anne Hathaway's cottage, Stratford-upon-Avon, England&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260423_HathawayCottage\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Shakespeare+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260422_1830\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260423_HathawayCottage"},"Ssd":"20260423","Name":"HathawayCottage","Market":"EN-IN","Hash":"1263350288","FullDateString":"23 Apr, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Earth Day didn't knock gently. It kicked the door wide open. In 1970, oilsoaked beaches, burning rivers and toxic air mobilised millions into street protests. When looking away was no longer an option, conservation was forced onto political agendas, sparking landmark environmental laws and flipping planetcare from fringe concern to global priority. Every 22 April, over 190 countries pause, reflect and reassess.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-IN0962469731_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_EN-IN0962469731_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The power of protest","Title":"Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Tartu County, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/58.466962,26.199884/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-IN&od=2&shading=flat&pp=58.466962,26.199884;S9;Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve, Tartu County, Estonia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:fa